<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="242" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phalaena roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">Phalaena roraria</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1776, Genera Insect. 285, Europe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phalaena adspersaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersaria">Phalaena adspersaria</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1787, Mantissa Insect. 2: 189, [Germany], [Saxony-Anhalt]: Halae Saxonum [Halle (Saale)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fidonia spartiaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spartiaria">Fidonia spartiaria</taxonomicName>
Treitschke, 1827, Schmett. Eur. 6 (1): 270, [Germany]: river Rhine [patria falsa?]. The original description (upperside and underside) corresponds to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">roraria</taxonomicName>
, but in the locality indicated only the taxon 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="limbaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbaria">limbaria</taxonomicName>
occurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="242" pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName authority="aequestriga" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fidonia roraria subsp. ab." order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="roraria" subSpecies="ab.">Fidonia roraria ab. aequestriga</taxonomicName>
Hirschke, 1910, Verh. zool.-bot. Ges. Wien 60: 416, [Czech Republic], Silesia: near Trop 
<pageBreakToken pageId="15" pageNumber="242" start="start">pau</pageBreakToken>
[Opava] [infrasubspecific: form without dark terminal fascia].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="242">
<taxonomicName authority="nigrescens" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fidonia roraria subsp. ab." order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="roraria" subSpecies="ab.">Fidonia roraria ab. nigrescens</taxonomicName>
Preissecker, 1923, Verh. zool.-bot. Ges. Wien 72: (95), [Lower Austria]: Dunkelsteinerwald, near Ernsthof [infrasubspecific].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="242">
? 
<taxonomicName authority="Duponchel, 1829" authorityName="Caradja" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cleogene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cleogene ostrogovichi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ostrogovichi">Cleogene ostrogovichi</taxonomicName>
Caradja, 1930, Bull. Sect. scient. Acad. roum. 13 (3): 52, [Romania], 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Siebenbürgen">Siebenbuergen</normalizedToken>
[Transylvania]: Cluj, [
<normalizedToken originalValue="Galişer">Galiser</normalizedToken>
Hill]. Synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Duponchel, 1829" authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cleogene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">roraria</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Rakosy, L" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica romanica" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" pagination="63 - 67" publicationUrl="http://er.lepidoptera.ro/20_2016/ER20201603_Rakosy_etal.pdf" refId="B30" refString="Rakosy, L, Stuening, D, Stănescu, M, Sommerer, M, 2016. The systematic position of Palaeocrocota ostrogovichi (Caradja, 1930) (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Ennominae). Entomologica romanica 20: 63 - 67, http://er.lepidoptera.ro/20_2016/ER20201603_Rakosy_etal.pdf" title="The systematic position of Palaeocrocota ostrogovichi (Caradja, 1930) (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Ennominae)." url="http://er.lepidoptera.ro/20_2016/ER20201603_Rakosy_etal.pdf" volume="20" year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rákosy">Rakosy</normalizedToken>
et al. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, but it could instead be synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Duponchel, 1829" authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cleogene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="rablensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rablensis">rablensis</taxonomicName>
if the occurrence of this taxon in the Cluj-Napoca area was ascertained.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="242">
<taxonomicName authority="stehliki" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Isturgia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isturgia roraria subsp. ab." order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="roraria" subSpecies="ab.">Isturgia roraria ab. stehliki</taxonomicName>
Bretschneider, 1954, Ent. Z. 64: 41, Germany, [Saxony-Anhalt], Dessau [infrasubspecific: almost completely black form, obtained from a F2 generation, bred from normal-coloured 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1776" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Isturgia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">roraria</taxonomicName>
parents].
</paragraph>
